page.title: 09ODD THINGS IN THE WOODS
page.content: IN THE AREA AROUND WOOLMERS AND IN CORPORATION WOODS SEVERAL INTERESTING THINGS CAN BE SEEN. THERE IS A FENCED OFF AREA USED TO REAR PHEASANTS BEFORE THEY ARE RELEASED. THE CORN FED TO THEM HAS IN SEVERAL PLACES SPROUTED. THERE ARE TWO WELLS, STILL FULL OF WATER, TAKING THEIR WATER FROM NATURAL SPRINGS. ONE OF THEM IS STILL IN USE AND HAS A TAP. THERE ARE SEVERAL APPARENTLY DERELICT SHEDS CONTAINING OLD PLOUGHS AND OTHER FARM IMPLEMENTS. BESIDE THE KENNELS AT WOOLMERS IS AN AREA OF HARDSTANDING WITH SEVERAL TRAILERS AND WAGONS. THE MOST INTERESTING FIND OF ALL IS A STEAM ROAD ROLLER. THIS STILL APPEARS TO BE IN USE; AS THERE ARE SOME CIRCULAR SAWS NEARBY WITH NO OTHER SOURCE OF POWER IT MAY BE THAT THE ENGINE IS USED FOR THAT PURPOSE.
